    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-15T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-15T05:00:00-05:00" n="771"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d771">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/17502: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States High Commissioner in the Philippines</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sayre</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Manila</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-15T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 15, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 15—7:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>628. Personal for [President] Roosevelt. Am gravely concerned over rumors
                    circulating here. Filipinos risking lives and country on faith of America’s word
                    she will protect them. Under MacArthur’s<note n="2" xml:id="d771fn2">Gen.
                        Douglas MacArthur, Commanding General, United States Army Forces in, the Far
                        East.</note>
                    <pb facs="0895" n="883" xml:id="pg_883"/> leadership they making magnificent
                    defense effort. America cannot afford to let them down. Whispers here United
                    States withholding further aid and does not intend to try break Jap blockade.
                    Existing forces woefully inadequate. Assume whispers untrue but if they become
                    convincing there’s critical danger of collapse entire structure and ensuing
                    disaster. To avert this may I suggest, first, that you forthwith order available
                    resources be sent succor Philippines; second, you publicly announce this fact,
                    giving lie to rumors and preserving morale here. Immediate action necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sayre</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
